e at times varied our systems of transliteration. The method set forth in Nabokov’s translation of Alexander Pushkin’s Eugene Onegin is probably the clearest and most logical of these variants. Except where accepted usage dictates a different form, or where Nabokov himself has digressed from that system, it is the one I have generally used.

Dmitri Nabokov





